# Pin text sources to LF in the working tree.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   - gofmt is LF-only. It has no CRLF mode and never will.
#   - core.autocrlf=true (set machine-wide on some dev machines) silently
#     rewrites the WORKING TREE to CRLF on every checkout, even though the
#     stored blobs are already LF. gofmt then flags every converted file, which
#     trained us to treat "not gofmt-clean" as the normal state and stop
#     formatting.
#   - It also made `git stash` destructive: a `stash pop` rewrote every .go
#     file to CRLF mid-edit and had to be repaired by hand.
#
# `eol=lf` pins the working tree to LF regardless of core.autocrlf, so gofmt
# and git stop fighting. The stored blobs are ALREADY LF, so this changes no
# committed content and rewrites nothing existing -- it only stops the
# checkout-time conversion that was corrupting the working tree.

*.go     text eol=lf
go.mod   text eol=lf
go.sum   text eol=lf
*.md     text eol=lf
